FBIS3-35493 "drnes038_l_94005" FBIS-NES-94-038 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Feb 1994 ISRAEL Gunman Kills Over 50 Arabs at Hebron Mosque 25 Feb `Rebels Movement' Assumes Responsibility TA2502070894 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0658 GMT 25 Feb 94 TA2502070894 Tel Aviv IDF Radio Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] A previously unknown movement, the Rebels Movement [Tnu'at Hamordim], an extreme Jewish movement whose members apparently belong to or are affiliated in some way with the Kakh Movement, called IDF Radio's news studio a short time ago and assumed responsibility for the massacre in Hebron. The anonymous caller said that the Rebels Movement assumes responsibility for the massacre committed to avenge the slaying of Rabbi Me'ir Kahana, the late leader of the Kakh Movement.
